{
  "texts": [
    "However, it should be mention that nTSNTM requires specific pre-processed data.",
    "But since the preprocessed data are only available for NG20 and Reuters, the experiments could only be carried out on these datasets.",
    "Moreover, as nTSNTM does not provide topic words, only evaluation measures computable from the produced results are reported.",
    "Experimental Results Results for Flat Topic DetectionTopic coherence and diversity analysis This first set of experiments allows to compare Community Topic (CT) with other popular topic modeling algorithms, namely LDA, Top2Vec, BERTopic, and CorEx for flat topics discovery.",
    "Table 1 presents a clear picture of the topic coherence and diversity scores obtained with these algorithms."
  ]
}